notes: To serve, divide the meatloaves, roasted carrots, and mashed cauliflower between plates. Enjoy!
directions:
**Prep and Bake Meatloves**

Preheat the oven to 425°F.

Peel and mince onion; place in a medium bowl.

Add ground beef, eggs, milk, almond meal, salt, and pepper to the bowl with the onions. Mix with your hands until well combined.

Place ketchup and Dijon in a small bowl; stir to combine.
- _3 tbsp ketchup_
- _2 tsp Dijon mustard_

Divide meatloaf mixture between 12 muffin cups and top with ketchup glaze. Place in the oven and bake until cooked through, 20-25 minutes.

**Prep and Cook Cauliflower**

Meanwhile, fill a medium saucepan with about 1-inch of hot water (from the tap); cover and place over high heat.

Wash cauliflower and cut off the leaves. Roughly chop into bite-sized florets and cut stems into smaller pieces.

Once the water in the saucepan is boiling, add cauliflower, reduce heat to medium, cover, and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.

**Prep and Roast Carrots**

Meanwhile, wash, trim, and peel carrots. Slice lengthwise into quarters. Place on a baking sheet pan, drizzle with oil, and season with salt and pepper. Place in the oven and bake until golden and fork-tender, 10-12 minutes.

**Mash Cauliflower**

When the cauliflower is cooked, drain in a colander and transfer to a blender. Add butter, salt, and pepper; purée until smooth. Work in batches, if necessary, to bestfit your blender.
name: Mini Glazed Meatloaves with Mashed Cauliflower & Roasted Carrots
ingredients:
6 medium carrots
1 medium head cauliflower
2 eggs
1 ½ lb lean ground beef (or turkey)
4 fl oz whole milk
1 medium yellow onion
 almond meal/flour
 black pepper
 butter, unsalted
 Dijon mustard
 extra virgin olive oil
 ketchup
 salt
